@page "/cli"
<PageTitle>CLI &amp; MSBuild — Settex</PageTitle>

<h1>CLI &amp; MSBuild</h1>
<p class="lead">Compile <code>.settex</code> files from the command line, or automatically as part of a build.</p>

<h2 id="cli">CLI</h2>
<p>Install the global tool:</p>
<CodeBlock Lang="bash" Code="dotnet tool install --global Settex.Cli" />

<p>Compile a file — output goes next to it by default, or into a directory with <code>-o</code>:</p>
<CodeBlock Lang="bash" Code="@CliUsage" />

<p>The CLI reports precise, clickable diagnostics with file, line and column:</p>
<CodeBlock Lang="text" Code="@("appsettings.settex(12,5): error: Expected '=' after path")" />

<h2 id="msbuild">MSBuild integration</h2>
<p>
    Add the <code>Settex.Build</code> package and every <code>*.settex</code> file in the project is
    compiled on build. Diagnostics surface as MSBuild errors/warnings (code <code>SETTEX</code>), so a
    broken config fails the build.
</p>
<CodeBlock Lang="bash" Code="dotnet add package Settex.Build" />

<h3 id="customise">Customising the build</h3>
<CodeBlock Lang="xml" Code="@MsBuildConfig" />

<h2 id="output">Output &amp; source control</h2>
<p>
    A typical project keeps the <code>.settex</code> source under version control and lets the build
    regenerate the JSON:
</p>
<CodeBlock Lang="text" Code="@Structure" />
<p>Add <code>*.settex</code> to source control and either ignore the generated JSON or commit it for deployment.</p>

@code {
    private const string CliUsage = """
        # Compile a file (output next to it)
        settex build appsettings.settex

        # Specify an output directory
        settex build config.settex -o ./output

        # Help
        settex --help
        settex build --help
        """;

    private const string MsBuildConfig = """
        <PropertyGroup>
          <!-- Change output directory (default: project root) -->
          <SettexOutputDirectory>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\config</SettexOutputDirectory>

          <!-- Disable automatic compilation -->
          <EnableSettexCompilation>false</EnableSettexCompilation>
        </PropertyGroup>

        <!-- Or specify files explicitly -->
        <ItemGroup>
          <SettexFile Include="config\app.settex" />
          <SettexFile Include="config\services.settex" />
        </ItemGroup>
        """;

    private const string Structure = """
        MyProject/
        ├── appsettings.settex           # source (in version control)
        ├── appsettings.json             # generated (base)
        ├── appsettings.Development.json  # generated (base + dev)
        ├── appsettings.Production.json   # generated (base + prod)
        └── MyProject.csproj
        """;
}
